SIMPLE: gobble
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gobble
<hw>Gob"ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Gobbled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Gobbling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Freq. of 2d
<ets>gob</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To swallow or eat greedily or hastily; to
gulp.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Supper <qex>gobbled</qex> up in haste.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To utter (a sound) like a turkey cock.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He . . . <qex>gobbles</qex> out a note of self-approbation.</q>
<rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To gobble up</b></col>, <cd>to capture in a mass or in
masses; to capture suddenly.</cd> <mark>[Slang]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gobble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Gobble
<hw>Gob"ble</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To eat
greedily.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make a noise like that of a turkey cock.</def>
<rj><au>Prior.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gobble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Gobble
<hw>Gob"ble</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A noise made in the
throat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ducks and geese . . . set up a discordant <qex>gobble</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Mrs. Gore.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>gobbledygook</ent>⟦br⟧
